description:
Welcome to our channel, Melodies of History.

This channel was founded by two friends passionate about music. Our goal is not industrial mainstream music, but rather to discover and recreate the incredible, often overlooked musical treasures from around the world. We personally play instruments such as the drum, ney, duduk, and tembur.

In our music production, we make use of Kurdmed Berlin Studio, as well as platforms like LANDR, LABS, Google, Soundtrap, Suno, and a few other digital tools. From Africa to the Americas, Anatolia to Australia, we are deeply inspired by the traditional music of ancient cultures and lands.

All of our content is produced entirely by us and is subject to copyright in case of reuse.
For any inquiries, feel free to contact us at lucasmarwel@gmail.com


Support us on this journey by liking our content and subscribing to our channel.
Stay with music ‚Äî for peace and love.



Warning! None of the music on this channel was created by Indigenous peoples.
